pr_review_body:
@cyfdecyf Thank you very much for continuing to enhance `Sequence` support!

> Test cases are added now. It's a little hacky because I'm not familiar with the use cases.

No problem! I can slightly refactor them later. Don't want to delay this PR.

Looks ok to me, thanks @bhushan-borole!

@djmitche Can you give this a look too?

My only thought is whether we might want to include the minimum postgres version in some external file that we read in, so we have a config file we can update if we want to change it, rather than needing to change it inline.

My only question here is around config, given that it is read from environment variables. It looks like you've already taken care of this by adding a new method manage config directly for inline programs: https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/pull/5761/files#diff-21f2270d821d960ebfe77162b8b0013d03bb5daae6a9d053328b806fed3c0110

Nice! 

@mikhailshilkov any additional feedback or are we ready to merge this?
